Explore Analytics (detection rule)

To detect malicious activities, Microsoft Sentinel generally relies on detection rules. These rules are called "Analytics". The analytics, like the workbooks, are developed with KQL.

Go to Analytics.

Figure - zoom in


Active rules are the detection rules that are already enabled and detect malicious activities. In addition, you can use a large set of Analytics shared by Microsoft and the information security community from the "Rule templates" section.

You will see the following analytics on the Active rules page: RDP Brute Force Attack Detection.
